<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Host2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Host,</orth> subst. (never immediately preceded by the indef. art.; only once the poss. pron. <emph>my</emph> immediately before it, <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 2, 50</bibl>; else <emph>mine</emph> and <emph>thine</emph>) 1) one who hospitably lodges and entertains another at his house: <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 1, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.9.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 9, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.6.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 6, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.7.14" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 7, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.7.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 7, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 2</bibl>.<lb />2) an innkeeper, a landlord: <cit><quote>a mad h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.1.115" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 1, 115</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the h. of the Garter,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.1.115" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 1, 115</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.80" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.518" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 518</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.31" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.165" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 165</bibl>. Used as a vocative: <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 2, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 2, 73</bibl> <emph>to lie at h.</emph> == to be put up at an inn: <cit><quote>our goods that lay at h. in the Centaur,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 5.410" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 410</bibl></cit>. Mostly preceded by <emph>my</emph> and <emph>mine</emph>: <cit><quote>mine h. of the Garter,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 143</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.4.124" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.100" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 95</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.3.256" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 256</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.75" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.75" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 75</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 4</bibl>. <cit><quote>my h. at Saint Albans,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 2, 50</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my ranting h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.196" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 196</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.196" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 196</bibl> In the vocative: <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 2, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 1</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.199" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 199</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.199" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 199</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.199" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 199</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.1.93" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.26" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.26" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 26</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 30</bibl> <cit><quote>my good h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.6.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 6, 47</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.13" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.211" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 211</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.6.18" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 18</bibl>. <cit><quote>thine h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.19" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 19</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>